# The image COMPILES NOTHING — it copies a prebuilt binary. So the whole build
# context is just the binary plus the runtime assets.
#
# What must NOT be excluded, and why:
#   dist/       the CI-built release binary; the image is nothing without it
#   plugins/    per-plugin templates, found at runtime via a baked absolute path
#   static/     includes the committed, pre-built static/css/umbral.css
#   .prod.env   baked in as /app/.env (on the server, where the secret lives)
#   templates/ migrations/

# Build artefacts and sources. The binary is prebuilt, so none of this is needed
# to assemble the runtime image.
/target
/src
/build.rs
/styles
/Cargo.toml
/Cargo.lock

# Local SQLite dev database.
/umbral_website.db*

# Runtime uploads live in the `media` named volume, never in an image layer.
/media

# The local dev env (SQLite, Dev environment). Baking it would shadow .prod.env.
/.env

# Secrets that must never enter an image layer: the age private key, and the
# encrypted form of .prod.env (the image gets the decrypted one).
/keys.txt
/secret.env

# Dev-only settings. It declares `environment = "Dev"`, which would override the
# release binary's secure `Prod` default. Production reads /app/.env only.
/umbral.toml

# Repo + design assets, irrelevant to the running site.
/.git
/.github
/design
